        "id": "SKESTDC001-DN526744-25923489",
        "title": "CCTV at Temporary Accommodation (South Kesteven District Council)",
        "description": "South Kesteven District Council is seeking quotes for the supply of upgrades and/or new installations to their temporary accommodation CCTV systems to ensure that they are fit for purpose. \r\n\r\nThe CCTV system across the temporary accommodation needs to be sufficient to ensure the safety of Council officers attending the accommodation and provide evidence to the Police in the event of a criminal or anti-social incident. The CCTV system will be required to have a remote connection and is being installed to protect the premises and residents from theft, vandalism, anti-social behaviour. It will also be required to track and record accidental or wilful damage and to provide additional monitoring for health and safety purposes.\r\n\r\nThe detailed requirements are defined in the quotation documents, please formally register your interest in this opportunity to access the full documentation. \r\n\r\nThe deadline for completed tender submissions to be received on the eTendering Portal is 12:00 noon on 5th March 2021. \r\n\r\nThe Contract is due to commence on 1st April 2021. \r\n\r\nPLEASE NOTE: Bidders are required to make arrangements to undertake a supervised site visit to the sites which need the 230vac, to review wiring routes prior to the submission of quotations to ensure their accuracy (please see 2.8 of Document One for site details and further information). Attendance at a site visit is mandatory as part of this procurement process, and all site visits must be conducted in line with any local and national COVID legislation and guidance. The Council reserves the right to eliminate bids from the procurement process (without evaluation), that are received from any bidder that has not attended a site visit. Site visits must be arranged through the messaging function of the project on ProContract. The deadline for submitting a request for attending a site visit is 26th February 2021 (to ensure the Council is able to arrange a suitable site visit (in terms of date and time), we would encourage you to submit your request as early as possible).",
